API Gateway is a front door also called main entry point, that sits in between client and the backend services.
  Embracing gateway enables in Hiding complexities of the services in the backend.
  The Gateway handles routing request to the appropriate server.
  Aggregating data from different services
  Applying policies constantly across all services.

Main Roles and Responsibilities of API Gateway
    - Routing: Forward requests to the server using URL,content and business rules.
    - Security: applies Authorization/authentication, access controls and Threat prevention
    - Orchestration- Service discovery, handling failure using retries, circuit breaker and scheduling
    - Trafic control: Load balancing, rate limiting,caching
    - Observability: Monitoring, logging, tracing



